Boil @water{350%ml} in a #pot (in preparation for your rice). Chop the root from your @Pak Choi{2} and separate the individual leaves. Place the flat side of a large #knife on your @garlic{1%clove} and press down firmly to release the skin. Peel and chop the garlic finely. Finally, very thinly slice your @British chicken thighs{4}.

Add your @basmati rice{1%cup} to the pot along with the @coconut powder{3%tbsp}, cover with a tight #lid and cook on low for ~{10%minutes}, then rest off the heat for ~{10%minutes}. Don't peek under the lid until 20 mins are up!

> Tip: It doesn't matter if you don't finish cooking everything else before the rice is ready...it will wait!

Put a #non-stick pan{} on medium-high heat and toast the @cashew nuts{2%tbsp}.

> Tip: Watch your nuts like a sheepdog watching its flock, because they can burn really easily.

Remove them from the pan and keep to the side for later.

Peel the piece of @ginger{1%piece} using the edge of a #spoon. Now finely dice up the peeled ginger.

To make your teriyaki sauce, simply mix the @honey{1/2%tbsp}, garlic, @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} and ginger together thoroughly in a #bowl with @water{1%tbsp}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in your non-stick pan on high heat until it is almost smoking. Cook your chicken in two batches for ~{2%minutes} to brown it off.

> Tip: Cooking it in batches will mean the pan isn't overcrowded, so the meat will brown off instead of stewing.

Put all the chicken into the pan and add in the teriyaki sauce. Continue to cook for ~{2%minutes} before adding in the bok choy. After another ~{2%minutes}, the bok choy should have wilted and you're ready!

Fluff up your rice with a #fork and serve with your chicken and a sprinkling of toasted cashew nuts.